      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FARRAIGE (8) has won just once in 47 starts but this is not strong so he gets his chance. Came with a powerful finish to get up for second at his latest appearance over 1800m at Port Macquarie. Will have no trouble getting this trip. Prefers the sting out of the ground but in this company he comes out on top. LIBBY (5) made a mid-race move to join the lead then battled on well to hang on for second last time out over 1900m at Armidale. In the money two back over 2217m at Grafton so this trip holds no fears. Hasn't won for a while but this looks a nice race for her. QUIRKY PRINCESS (6) is a three-start maiden but did a fine job to finish second in a Class 1 over 2105m at Tuncurry recently. Has more upside than these and can break through without surprising. DIPIERDOMENICO (1) will appreciate getting out to this trip and can improve on some recent plain performances. TIPSY MISS (4) is yet to race beyond 1500m so this is uncharted waters. One for the exotics.",
